This project builds on two Apache-2.0 licensed repositories. `cao/ao_runtime.py` is a
clean reimplementation of their verified activation-injection / extraction / read-logprobs
semantics (the semantics were lifted, not the source files):

  - Activation Oracles — Karvonen et al., 2025
    https://github.com/adamkarvonen/activation_oracles  (Apache-2.0)
    arXiv:2512.15674

  - CoT Oracle — De Schamphelaere (ceselder), 2026
    https://github.com/ceselder/cot-oracle  (Apache-2.0)
    Released checkpoints: https://huggingface.co/ceselder

  - Building Better Activation Oracles — Bauer, De Schamphelaere, Karvonen, Luick, Nanda, 2026
    https://github.com/japhba/activation_oracles  (Apache-2.0)
    arXiv:2606.02609

The released oracle checkpoint (e.g. ceselder/cot-oracle-v15-stochastic) is a LoRA adapter
on Qwen/Qwen3-8B and is downloaded from HuggingFace at runtime; it is not redistributed here.
